message.content:
To find out how many cereal bits were used in each design, divide the total number of cereal bits (63) by the number of designs (9):

Number of cereal bits per design = Total cereal bits / Number of designs
= 63 / 9
= 7

Emily used 7 cereal bits in each design. Since she created an equal number of designs, it's reasonable to assume she used an equal number of cereal bits in each design.
